page.title: 01Trumpington - G. Shelford
page.content:
The Great Shelford to Trumpington road (A1301) is surrounded on either side by clustered housing. The waste land on both sides of the houses leads on to arable ground to the East.
In the distance is a{forestry plantation which carries on beyond the horizon. This square is mainly pasture and crops. { The{housing}along the road is fairly linear and is surrounded by one large field on both sides leading to the forestry plantation. In the middle of the plantation are a series of high rise offices, enclosed by pine trees on three sides. It is mainly pasture and forestry plantation.
